We identify that the spin of a particle corresponds specifically to rotations generated by the Universal-Spatial generators $\{T_{\tau x}, T_{\tau y}, T_{\tau z}\}$. These generators do not form an $\mathfrak{so}(3)$ subalgebra directly, but rather follow the general commutation relations for $SO(7)$ generators:

\begin{equation}
