Specifically, we can identify the three color states as follows:

\begin{align}
|r\rangle &\sim (x + it_x, 0, 0) \\
|g\rangle &\sim (0, y + it_y, 0) \\
|b\rangle &\sim (0, 0, z + it_z)
\end{align}

These states form a basis for the fundamental representation of $SU(3)$. The orthogonality of these states in the 6-dimensional subspace ensures that they transform appropriately under $SU(3)$ operations.

