where $\Psi_q$ is the 7D quark spinor field, $\Gamma^A$ are the 7D gamma matrices, $D_A$ is the gauge-covariant derivative (now including the $SU(3)$ connection), $m_q$ is the quark mass, $g^{(7)}$ is the determinant of the 7D metric, and $F_{\times}^{SU(3)}$ is the $SU(3)$ field strength.

The covariant derivative is:

\begin{equation}
D_A \Psi_q = \partial_A \Psi_q + \frac{1}{4}\omega_A^{BC}\Gamma_{BC} \Psi_q + A_{\times, A}^{SU(3)} \Psi_q
\end{equation}

where $\omega_A^{BC}$ are the spin connection coefficients, $\Gamma_{BC}$ are the generators of $SO(7)$ in the spinor representation, and $A_{\times, A}^{SU(3)}$ is the $SU(3)$ gauge connection.

\subsubsection{Projection to the 4D QCD Lagrangian}

When projected onto 4D spacetime, this action yields the conventional QCD Lagrangian:

\begin{equation}
\mathcal{L}_{QCD} = \bar{\psi}_q (i\hbar \gamma^\mu D_\mu - m_q c) \psi_q - \frac{1}{4} F_{\mu\nu}^a F^{a\mu\nu}
